{"cursor":"19461","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"]] with avionics laid out]] 'Avionics' are the electronic systems used on\naircraft, artificial satellites, and spacecraft.\n\nAvionic systems include communications, navigation, the display and management\nof multiple systems, and the hundreds of systems that are fitted to aircraft to\nperform individual functions. These can be as simple as a searchlight for a\npolice helicopter or as complicated as the tactical system for an airborne early\nwarning platform.\n\nThe term is a portmanteau of the words '[[aviation]]' and '[[electronics]]'.\n","linknr":390,"url":"Avionics","recorded":1362267860,"links":68,"instances":["communications_system"],"pdf":["http://www.jpdo.gov/library/20111005_ARM_complete_LowRes_v2.0.pdf","http://www.jpdo.gov/library/20111005_ARM_complete_LowRes_v2.0.pdf"],"categories":["Avionics|","Aircraft instruments","Spacecraft components"],"headings":["History","Aircraft avionics","Mission or tactical avionics","See also","Notes","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/08/Cessna501_radar.JPG/250px-Cessna501_radar.JPG","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Republic_F-105B_with_avionics_layout_060831-F-1234S-046.jpg/250px-Republic_F-105B_with_avionics_layout_060831-F-1234S-046.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ef/4thoperationsgroup-f-15es.jpg/250px-4thoperationsgroup-f-15es.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Airbus_A380_cockpit.jpg/250px-Airbus_A380_cockpit.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/st